{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φάσκω</b>, <br /> used by <i>Epic dialect</i> only in <i>imperfect</i> ἔφασκον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.100 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> φάσκον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.75, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 209: frequently in Trag. and Comedy texts (but perhaps never in _present_ _indicative_, see below)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: as <i>imperfect</i> of φημί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 110, etc., also 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 742; also _imperative_ φάσκε 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 1077, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica ad Alexandrum” 1429a6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>subjunctive</i> φάσκω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 93, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 561 (_anapaest meter_), 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.4.3, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 25.11, 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 10.11, “PHal.” 1.134 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>optative</i> φάσκοιμι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1037, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 30.27 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>infinitive</i> φάσκειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 9, “OT” 462, “Ph.” 1411 (_anapaest meter_), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 695 (troch.), 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.2.52, +others, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>participle</i> φάσκων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.66.6, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 1382 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (the only part of the Verb used in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus (3.70) and 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus (“R.” 337e, +others), except ἔφασκεν [prev. author] “Lg.” 901a)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i> is not found, ἐφάσκετ᾽ is for ἐφάσκετε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 114 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. Rare in <i>present</i> <i>indicative</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" before 3rd c.BC: φάσκει 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 6.16 (φάσκοι Reiske, Wyse), “PMich.Zen.” 82.6 (3rd c.BC), “PSI” 8.921.7 (2nd c.AD), uncertain in 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “Πυρρώνειοι ὑποτυπώσεις” 1.17 (variant{φάσκοι}), 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 15.35, “Geoponica” 9.14.2, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus; φάσκεις “PSI” 9.1011.10 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; φάσκουσι (ν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator “Epistulae” 11.11, “PCair.Zen.” 21.25, 244.5, +others (3rd c.BC), 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Antonius” 86, 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 10.429b, “Geoponica” 5.2.9, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; φάσκομεν is uncertain conjecture (for πάσχομεν) in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 146.4 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<b>say, affirm, assert,</b> with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.191, 8.565, +others\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; φάσκειν as <i>imperative</i>, in this <i>construction</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 462, “Ph.” 1411 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ φασκόντων χρήσειν <b>saying</b> they <b>would</b> not.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.58; οὐ φάσκων ἀνεκτὸν εἶναι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.52 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; the <i>infinitive</i> is frequently to be supplied, ἐν τῇδ᾽ ἔφασκε γῇ (i.e. εὑρεθήσεσθαι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 110 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φησίν γε· φάσκων δ᾽ (i.e. ἥξειν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “El.” 319 \">Refs</a>]; τῶν φασκόντων γονέων (i.e. εἶναι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 538a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; rarely φ. ὡς.., ὅτι.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Moschus Bucolicus 2.12, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.215f: with _accusative_, τοῦτο φ. τοὔπος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 93, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 1382, etc.: _absolutely_, ὡς ἔφασκεν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 114; φάσκουσα καὶ οὐ φάσκουσα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 190a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>think, deem, expect,</b> ὃ οὔ ποτ᾽ ἔγωγε τελευτήσεσθαι ἔφασκον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.100; οὔ μ᾽ ἐφάσκεθ᾽.. οἴκαδ᾽ ἱκέσθαι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.35 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; φάσκειν.. ὁρᾶν <b>believe that</b> you see, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 9. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>say, promise,</b> with <i>infinitive</i> <i>future</i>, με.. ἔφασκε θήσειν ἀθάνατον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.256; φάσκων προσποιήσειν αὐτήν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.85, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ion” 541e. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5335","accentedUnicode":"φάσκω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5346","matchingForm":"φημί","stepTransliteration":"fēmi","gloss":"to say","_zh_tw_Gloss":"說","_es_Gloss":"decir","_zh_Gloss":"说"}],"shortDef":"to claim, assert","mediumDef":"to claim, assert <br /><b>to assert, affirm,</b> <ref='Act.24.9'>Acts 24:9;</ref> 25:19; <ref='Rom.1.22'>Rom. 1:22</ref>*","stepGloss":"to claim","stepTransliteration":"faskō","count":3,"_es_Definition":"alegar, dec